<h2>How to Identify Authentic Filipino Products</h2>

<h3>Red Flags (Fake or Mass-Produced):</h3>

<ul>
<li>❌ Perfect uniformity (handmade has natural variations)</li>
<li>❌ Suspiciously cheap prices</li>
<li>❌ No information about artisan or origin</li>
<li>❌ Stock photos, no real product images</li>
<li>❌ Generic "handmade" claims without details</li>
</ul>

<h3>Green Flags (Authentic):</h3>

<ul>
<li>✅ Story about artisan/community</li>
<li>✅ Photos showing creation process</li>
<li>✅ Slight imperfections (proves handmade)</li>
<li>✅ Specific origin location mentioned</li>
<li>✅ Customer photos showing product variations</li>
<li>✅ Fair pricing (reflects labor and materials)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Questions to Ask Sellers:</h3>

